Description: CVE-2026-41989 - Fix decoding a point on Montgomery curve
 Libgcrypt before 1.11.3 has a heap-based buffer overflow in
 _gcry_ecc_mont_decodepoint() in cipher/ecc-misc.c. A crafted ECDH
 ciphertext to gcry_pk_decrypt can trigger an out-of-bounds write of
 2-54 zero bytes due to an incorrect memset destination offset when
 zero-padding decoded Curve25519 or X448 points. This patch corrects
 the memset offset and adds an update of rawmpilen after padding.
Origin: upstream, https://dev.gnupg.org/source/libgcrypt/commit/2d3d732c9bf87cc10729f69678dd9e6862f99fa3
Bug: https://dev.gnupg.org/T8211
Author: NIIBE Yutaka <gniibe@fsij.org>
Last-Update: 2026-04-26

--- a/cipher/ecc-misc.c
+++ b/cipher/ecc-misc.c
@@ -438,7 +438,10 @@ _gcry_ecc_mont_decodepoint (gcry_mpi_t pk, mpi_ec_t ec, mpi_point_t result)
         *--p = *buf++;

       if (rawmpilen < nbytes)
-        memset (rawmpi + nbytes - rawmpilen, 0, nbytes - rawmpilen);
+        {
+          memset (rawmpi + rawmpilen, 0, nbytes - rawmpilen);
+          rawmpilen = nbytes;
+        }
     }
   else
     {
